page.title: 02ECOLOGY 2 BIRDS AND FLOWERS
page.content: Wildlife is abundant in the area. There are many mammals such as vole, shrew, fieldmice, grey squirrel,fox, badger and rats to be found throughout the area. Birds sighted in the area include green plover,skylark,curlew, reedbunting,kingfisher,heron,housemart -in,swift,nightingale,woodcock, moorhen,mallard,coot,greater spotted wood-pecker,lesser spotted wood-pecker,green wood-pecker, gold finch,chaffinch,greenfinch,bullfinch, yellowhammer, kestrel,cuckoo, black- headed gull, herring gull, little owl, barn owl,tawny owl,magpie, jay, starling,rook,crow,songthrush, mistle- thrush,robin,and pheasant. Flowers are on the increase, particu- larly since the council introduced the metre cut, although there are no five star rarities. There is no significant pollution.{
